{"uuid":"f647102d-eb5e-4094-be7a-0d3d88481aee","name":"Multiple Oscar nominations for one film","summary":"","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","created_at":"2026-06-20T06:46:22.177627Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:58.606752Z","settings":{"enabled_web_search":true,"enabled_monkeys_in_a_barrel":true,"tool_search_mode":"auto","preview_feature_uses_artifacts":true,"enabled_artifacts_attachments":false,"enabled_turmeric":true,"thinking_mode":"auto","effort_level":"low"},"is_starred":false,"is_temporary":false,"platform":"CLAUDE_AI","is_wiggle_enabled":true,"effective_thinking_mode":"auto","current_leaf_message_uuid":"019ee3ca-f2d4-74df-9ae1-b62939deac03","chat_messages":[{"uuid":"019ee3c7-c8c7-70f6-8996-ce1dcf4ba80b","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:46:23.220434Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:46:23.220434Z","type":"text","text":"Can 1 single movie be nominated for multiple times in for Oscars?","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":0,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:46:23.223674Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:46:23.223674Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000000"},{"uuid":"019ee3c7-c8c7-752b-aba3-06bfc0f1ac0a","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:46:23.214475Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:46:29.344574Z","type":"text","text":"Yes, a single movie can receive multiple Oscar nominations — and this is actually quite common. Here's how it works:\n\n**Multiple Categories**\nA film can be nominated in as many categories as it qualifies for. For example, a movie could simultaneously be nominated for Best Picture, Best Director, Best Actor, Best Actress, Best Screenplay, Best Cinematography, Best Score, and so on — all in the same year.\n\n**Record Holders**\nSome films have received an enormous number of nominations in a single year:\n- *All About Eve* (1950) and *Titanic* (1997) each received **14 nominations**\n- *La La Land* (2016) also tied that record with **14 nominations**\n- *Everything Everywhere All at Once* (2023) received **11 nominations** and won 7\n\n**Same Film, Multiple Years?**\nA film can only be nominated in the year it becomes eligible (based on its release/qualifying run). It **cannot** be re-nominated in a later year for the same work.\n\n**Same Category, Multiple Nominations?**\nA single film can even have **multiple nominations within the same category**. For instance, a film could have two actors nominated for Best Supporting Actor, or two songs nominated for Best Original Song.\n\nSo in short, one movie racking up 10–14 nominations in a single Oscar cycle is entirely possible and has happened several times throughout history.","citations":[]}],"sender":"assistant","index":1,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:46:29.371164Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:46:29.371164Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c7-c8c7-70f6-8996-ce1dcf4ba80b"},{"uuid":"019ee3c8-c2d9-7bce-8264-e672e41e79b5","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.192557Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.192557Z","type":"text","text":"Which film has been nominated the max times?","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":2,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.194517Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.194517Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c7-c8c7-752b-aba3-06bfc0f1ac0a"},{"uuid":"019ee3c8-c2d9-7873-89b7-f8c9bff07515","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.187701Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.979526Z","type":"text","text":"Let me search for the most up-to-date and accurate information on this.","citations":[]},{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.979590Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:47:27.981917Z","type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QkV2f1ttJJPkgY9AfFZE2e","name":"web_search","input":{"query":"film most Oscar nominations all time record"},"me