t just edge it out, it beat the old record by **two full categories**.\n\n---\n\n## Previous Record Holders (14 nominations each)\n\nThree films had previously shared the record of 14 nominations:\n\n- 🎬 ***All About Eve*** (1950) — Set the record that stood for 75 years\n- 🚢 ***Titanic*** (1997) — Tied the record\n- 🎵 ***La La Land*** (2016) — Also tied the record\n\n---\n\n## Other Notable High-Nomination Films\n\n| Film | Nominations |\n|---|---|\n| *Sinners* (2025) | **16** *(current record)* |\n| *All About Eve*, *Titanic*, *La La Land* | 14 each |\n| *Lord of the Rings: Fellowship of the Ring* | 13 |\n| *Ben-Hur*, *The Revenant*, and others | 12 each |\n\n*Sinners* is a remarkable achievement — a genre-defying historical vampire musical drama that managed to rack up more Oscar nominations than any film in the nearly 100-year history of the Academy Awards.","citations":[{"uuid":"c5dd710e-5984-42c2-a474-03b5d26123b6","title":"What film has received the most Oscar nominations? | Britannica","url":"https://www.britannica.com/question/What-film-has-received-the-most-Oscar-nominations","metadata":{"type":"webpage_metadata","site_domain":"britannica.com","favicon_url":"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=britannica.com","site_name":"Britannica"},"origin_tool_name":"web_search","sources":[{"title":"What film has received the most Oscar nominations? | Britannica","url":"https://www.britannica.com/question/What-film-has-received-the-most-Oscar-nominations","icon_url":"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=britannica.com","source":"Britannica","uuid":"c5dd710e-5984-42c2-a474-03b5d26123b6"}],"start_index":121,"end_index":422},{"uuid":"7162e508-41dc-4215-a574-ad1850f74447","title":"Every Film That Held the Record for Most Oscar Nominations, Up to 'Sinners'","url":"https://www.thewrap.com/creative-content/movies/movies-with-most-oscar-nominations/","metadata":{"type":"webpage_metadata","site_domain":"thewrap.com","favicon_url":"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=thewrap.com","site_name":"TheWrap"},"origin_tool_name":"web_search","sources":[{"title":"Every Film That Held the Record for Most Oscar Nominations, Up to 'Sinners'","url":"https://www.thewrap.com/creative-content/movies/movies-with-most-oscar-nominations/","icon_url":"https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?sz=64&domain=thewrap.com","source":"TheWrap","uuid":"7162e508-41dc-4215-a574-ad1850f74447"}],"start_index":424,"end_index":606}],"citations_grouping_mode":"combine"}],"sender":"assistant","index":3,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:47:38.035186Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:47:38.035186Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c8-c2d9-7bce-8264-e672e41e79b5"},{"uuid":"019ee3c9-ba13-773e-a3a0-47855b834f61","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:30.859990Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:30.859990Z","type":"text","text":"Who nominates them?","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":4,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:48:30.862817Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:48:30.862817Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c8-c2d9-7873-89b7-f8c9bff07515"},{"uuid":"019ee3c9-ba13-7b75-8c95-bf9d168b9910","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:30.853242Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:31.241335Z","type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking about who nominates films for the Oscars. This is a straightforward factual question I can answer from my knowledge.","summaries":[{"summary":"Identified straightforward factual query about Oscar nomination process."}],"cut_off":false,"truncated":true},{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:31.241557Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:48:38.298084Z","type":"text","text":"## Who Nominates Films for the Oscars?\n\nThe nominations are made by **members of the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences (AMPAS)** — the organization that runs the Oscars.\n\n### How It Works\n\n- The Academy has roughly **10,000+ members**, all of whom are industry professionals — directors, actors, cinematographers, editors, composers, writers, and so on.\n- Members are divided into **branches** based on their craft (e.g., the Actors Branch, the Directors Branch, the Cinematographers Branch).\n- For most categories, **only members of the relevant branch** can nominate. For example:\n  - Only **actors** nominate in the acting categories\n  - Only **directors** nominate in the Best Director category\n  - Only **composers** nominate in the Best Score category\n- **Best Picture is the exception** — all Academy members across all branches can nominate for it.\n\n### The Voting Process\n\n1. **Nomination Round** — Members submit their nominations (usually a ranked/preferential ballot).\n2. **Nominations are tallied** and the top contenders (typically 5, sometimes up to 10 for Best Picture) are announced.\n3. **Final Voting Round** — All eligible Academy members vote for the winner in each category.\n\n### Who Can Join the Academy?\n\nMembership is **by invitation only**. You must be sponsored by existing members or have significant professional credits. The Academy has been actively working in recent years to make membership more **diverse and international**.\n\nSo in short, it's essentially **Hollywood professionals voting for their peers** — a peer-recognition system at its core.","citations":[]}],"sender":"assistant","index":5,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:48:38.333763Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:48:38.333763Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c9-ba13-773e-a3a0-47855b834f61"},{"uuid":"019ee3ca-f2d3-78f5-8678-ad395a36f90a","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:50.427445Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:50.427445Z","type":"text","text":"Is there any category of least nominated movies?","citations":[]}],"sender":"human","index":6,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:50.431433Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:50.431433Z","truncated":false,"attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3c9-ba13-7b75-8c95-bf9d168b9910"},{"uuid":"019ee3ca-f2d4-74df-9ae1-b62939deac03","text":"","content":[{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:50.419222Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:51.472857Z","type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if there's an official category for least nominated movies at the Oscars. There isn't really an official \"least nominated\" category. Let me think about this and answer directly without searching.","summaries":[{"summary":"Examined whether official Oscar category exists for least-nominated films."}],"cut_off":false,"truncated":true},{"start_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:51.473175Z","stop_timestamp":"2026-06-20T06:49:58.578352Z","type":"text","text":"There is **no official category** for \"least nominated\" films at the Oscars — the Academy only tracks and celebrates nominations and wins, not the lack of them. However, there are some interesting related concepts in the film world:\n\n## Related \"Anti-Award\" Concepts\n\n### 🍓 The Razzies (Golden Raspberry Awards)\nThe closest thing to an \"opposite Oscars\" is the **Razzies**, which:\n- Have been running since **1981**\n- Celebrate the **worst** films, performances, and directing of the year\n- Are announced the day **before** the Oscars every year\n- Have categories like Worst Picture, Worst Actor, Worst Director, etc.\n- Some films have even won both an Oscar and a Razzie in the same year!\n\n---\n\n## Interesting \"Snub\" Phenomena\n\nRather than a formal category, film culture has developed informal terms for notable Oscar absences:\n\n- **\"Oscar Snub\"** — When a widely praised film or performance receives fewer nominations than expected, or none at all\n- **\"Box Office hits vs. Oscar nominees\"** — Many massively popular films are rarely nominated (e.g., superhero movies)\n- **\"0 nominations\"** — Some hugely successful films like *The Dark Knight* initially got no major nominations, causing public outcry\n\n---\n\n## The Bottom Line\n\nThe Oscars are purely about **recognizing the best**, so there's no formal mechanism for tracking the least nominated. But the Razzies, Oscar snub discussions, and pop culture commentary fill that gap unofficially. Would you like to know more about the Razzies or famous Oscar snubs?","citations":[]}],"sender":"assistant","index":7,"created_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:58.606752Z","updated_at":"2026-06-20T06:49:58.606752Z","truncated":false,"stop_reason":"end_turn","attachments":[],"files":[],"sync_sources":[],"parent_message_uuid":"019ee3ca-f2d3-78f5-8678-ad395a36f90a"}]}